<title>CHINA: Worldbest 1996 net surges 135.69 pct.</title>
<headline>Worldbest 1996 net surges 135.69 pct.</headline>
<dateline>SHANGHAI 1997-03-24</dateline>
<text>
<p>Year ended December 31, 1996</p>
<p>(in millions of yuan unless stated, against 1995 figures)</p>
<p> Turnover		   405.48	vs	  436.731</p>
<p> Net profit		 79.087	vs	  33.555</p>
<p> Net asset per share    2.017 yuan  vs	  1.95 yuan</p>
<p> Earnings per share     0.404 yuan	    not available</p>
<p>Full company name: Shanghai Worldbest Co Ltd</p>
<p>Note: the results were published in a company statement issued on Monday. The post-tax profit figure is based on international accounting standards and the other figures on domestic accounting standards.</p>
<p>Based on domestic accounting standards, the 1996 net was 80.24 million yuan.</p>
<p>The company listed foreign currency B shares on the Shanghai Stock Exchange on July 26, 1996.</p>
<p>The company's board of director proposes a pre-tax cash dividend of 0.105 yuan per share for B share holders.</p>
